      <ol>
        <li>
          <p>
            Consider the following statement written in symbolic form:
            <m>\left( {\forall x \in \mathbb{Z}} \right)\left( {x\text{ is a multiple of 2 } } \right)</m>.
            <ol>
              <li>
                <p>
                  Write this statement as an English sentence.
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  Is the statement true or false?
                  Why?
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  How would you write the negation of this statement as an English sentence?
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  If possible,
                  write your negation of this statement from part<nbsp/>(2) symbolically
                  (using a quantifier).
                </p>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Consider the following statement written in symbolic form:
            <m>\left( {\exists x \in \mathbb{Z}} \right)\left( {x^3 > 0} \right)</m>.
            <ol>
              <li>
                <p>
                  Write this statement as an English sentence.
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  Is the statement true or false?
                  Why?
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  How would you write the negation of this statement as an English sentence?
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  If possible,
                  write your negation of this statement from part<nbsp/>(2) symbolically
                  (using a quantifier).
                </p>
