        <cell>\Lower{<m>\left( {\forall x \in \mathbb{Z}} \right)\left( {\exists y \in \mathbb{Z}} \right)\left( {x + y = 0} \right)</m>}</cell>
        <cell>For every integer  <m>x</m>, there exists an integer  <m>y</m>  such that <m>x + y = 0</m>.</cell>
        <cell></cell>
      </row>
      <row>
